cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SI

Reasoning: The paper deals with entropic inequalities and their application to marginal problems, which are fundamental concepts in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves computational methods for solving marginal problems, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the application of entropic inequalities to graphical models, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
